cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D face tracking and reconstruction from images. It also involves graphics applications such as character generation and animation, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of autoencoders suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper involves mesh sampling operations, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of a multivariate Gaussian distribution suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
